Well, a lot of colleges won't hold the scholarships for a student who doesn't accept them right away...  and in these times, the costs of attendance are pretty stiff.  

But based on our experiences, college visitations were very helpful in sorting out where to apply (or not)...and the scholarships also affected the final decisions.  (In one case, an acceptance arrived with a very businesslike list of "Send this $$, fill out that form, send a final transcript" ...in great contrast to a very warm, welcoming acceptance that envisioned broad studies and growth....  PhysDaughter attended the latter.  I shared a copy of that acceptance letter with the first college... and later received a note thanking me and describing the changes they had made...)

